  <title>The Little Computer - Assembly</title>
  <p>The Little Computer supports an <xref ref="programming-languages_assembly-languages" text="custom">assembly language</xref> that can make it easier for humans
    to write and read programs. In addition to replacing numeric commands like &#8220;1XX&#8221; or &#8220;902&#8221;
    with abbreviated English commands like &#8220;ADD&#8221; or &#8220;OUT&#8221;, Little Computer assembly allows us to
    think at a slightly more abstract level. Instead of remembering specific memory addresses so we can say <em>&#8220;add
    the value from location 10&#8221;</em>, we can name memory locations and then say things like <em>&#8220;add
    X&#8221;</em>. This video introduces it:</p>

  <video xml:id="gg4siPI0sdk" youtube="gg4siPI0sdk" width="100%" />
